From 5cd346922e7517e5bdc592a56157707028965aa1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 20:07:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add onUnknownClass + onSerializeUnknown hooks

For host integration with the webgl-app-framework addon system: when an
abstract(...) field references a struct whose JS class isn't registered
(e.g. its addon is disabled), the host installs onUnknownClass to
provide a placeholder class. read_object walks the file's stored schema
to populate the placeholder's dynamic properties with all original
fields, so no data is lost.

For the matching write path, onSerializeUnknown lets the host name an
override struct (typically the original missing class) so that
write_struct re-emits the data under the original struct id + schema.

Default behavior unchanged when hooks are not installed.

Changes:
- src/struct_intern.ts: STRUCT class gains onUnknownClass +
  onSerializeUnknown fields. read_object uses onUnknownClass and the
  file's schema when the class is missing.
- src/struct_intern2.ts: StructTStructField pack honors
  onSerializeUnknown to override struct id/schema. unpack/unpackInto
  pass the numeric id through when class is missing so read_object can
  call the hook, then stamp _origClsname on the resulting placeholder
  instance.
- build/: rebuilt via rollup_module.config.js.

All 33 existing nstructjs tests still pass.
